post_cb({"41030249": {"ParentId": "41029092", "CommentCount": "1", "Body": "<p>It doesn't matter whether standard library algorithms use it or not. What matters is what the standard says in [meta.type.synop]/1:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_41029092_41030249_0\">The behavior of a program that adds specializations for any of the templates defined in this subclause is undefined unless otherwise specified.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Included in \"this subclause\" are all of the type-traits classes, including <code>decay</code>. So don't specialize it. Ever.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "734069", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "41030249", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2016-12-08T01:23:04.317", "LastActivityDate": "2016-12-08T01:23:04.317"}, "41029092": {"CommentCount": "1", "ViewCount": "62", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "734069", "CreationDate": "2016-12-07T23:14:42.573", "LastActivityDate": "2016-12-08T01:24:12.807", "Title": "Does it make sense to specialize std::decay?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "41030249", "LastEditDate": "2016-12-08T01:24:12.807", "Id": "41029092", "Score": "0", "Body": "<p>I have class that represents an array reference (<code>class array_ref</code>) and another that <em>is</em> (i.e. holds/own/contains) the array (<code>class array</code>). \n<code>array_ref</code> behaves like a reference.</p>\n<p>Does it make sense to specialize <code>std::decay</code> for <code>class array_ref</code> to be <code>array</code>?</p>\n<pre><code>namespace std{\ntemplate&lt;&gt; class decay&lt;arra_ref&gt;{typedef array type;};\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>What other alternatives do I have to tell generic programs that <code>array</code> is the \"value type\" of <code>array_ref</code>?</p>\n<p>Is <code>std::decay</code> used in any STL algorithm?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><template-specialization><c++-standard-library>", "OwnerUserId": "225186", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_41029092_41030249_0": {"section_id": 4695, "quality": 0.9, "length": 9}}, "n3337": {"so_41029092_41030249_0": {"section_id": 4504, "quality": 0.9, "length": 9}}, "n4659": {"so_41029092_41030249_0": {"section_id": 6090, "quality": 0.9, "length": 9}}}});